import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar('Average Distance', avg_distance, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(avg_distance, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['route'] = data['origin'] + ' to ' + data['destination']
    route_counts = data['route'].value_counts().sort_values(ascending=False)
    top_routes = route_counts.head(10)
    top_routes_df = pd.DataFrame({'route': top_routes.index, 'count': top_routes.values})
    pivot_table = top_routes_df.pivot(index='route', columns='count', values='count')
    pivot_table = pivot_table.fillna(0)
    plt.pcolor(pivot_table, cmap='Blues')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    plt.ylabel('Route')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination routes are the most popular?', wrap=True)
    plt.colorbar()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data.groupby('route')['delay'].apply(list), labels=data['route'].unique())
    ax.set_xlabel('Route')
    ax.set_ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of delay time by route?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
